<i>noun</i>: 화합 [화합], 화평 [화평], 화음 [화음], 화목 [화목], 화기 [화기], 합심 [합씸], 하모니 [], 친화 [친화], 총화 [총ː화], 조화 [조ː화], 융화 [융화] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화합 [화합]</dt><br>
<dd>harmony; concord; unison</dd><br>
<dd>사이좋게 어울림.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of mixing well with each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화평 [화평]</dt><br>
<dd>1. peace; harmony</dd><br>
<dd>마음속이나 사람들 사이에 갈등이 없이 평화로움.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which one is mentally peaceful or lives at peace with others without any conflict.</dd><br>
<dd>2. peace; harmony</dd><br>
<dd>나라 사이에 충돌이나 전쟁이 없이 평화로움.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which two or more countries are at peace with each other without any conflict or war.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화음 [화음]</dt><br>
<dd>chord; harmony</dd><br>
<dd>높이가 서로 다른 둘 이상의 음이 함께 어울리는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>A pleasing sound produced when two or more musical notes blend well with each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화목 [화목]</dt><br>
<dd>harmony; concord; peace</dd><br>
<dd>서로 뜻이 맞고 정다움.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of agreeing with each other and being friendly toward each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화기 [화기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. warm temperature</dd><br>
<dd>따뜻하고 화창한 기온.</dd><br>
<dd>The warm temperature on a sunny day.</dd><br>
<dd>2. geniality; amicability; harmony</dd><br>
<dd>온화한 얼굴빛. 또는 화목한 분위기.</dd><br>
<dd>Mild countenance or harmonious atmosphere.</dd><br>
<dd>3. glow; radiance; luster</dd><br>
<dd>밝고 건강한 얼굴빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A bright and healthy look appearing on one's face.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>합심 [합씸]</dt><br>
<dd>concurrence; harmony; cooperation</dd><br>
<dd>여러 사람이 마음을 하나로 모음.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of putting different people's minds or opinions together.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>하모니 []</dt><br>
<dd>1. harmony</dd><br>
<dd>여러 물건이나 일 등이 미적으로 서로 잘 어울림.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which many objects or works, etc., aesthetically mix well with each other.</dd><br>
<dd>2. harmony</dd><br>
<dd>음악에서 여러 음들이 함께 날 때의 어울림.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which different musical notes blend well with each other to produce a pleasing sound.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>친화 [친화]</dt><br>
<dd>harmony; friendship; affinity</dd><br>
<dd>서로 친하게 잘 어울림.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of being on friendly terms and in harmony with one another.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>총화 [총ː화]</dt><br>
<dd>1. harmony; unity</dd><br>
<dd>전체의 화합.</dd><br>
<dd>The harmony of the whole.</dd><br>
<dd>2. aggregate; total</dd><br>
<dd>전체를 하나로 합쳐서 셈. 또는 그 계산.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of adding up all numbers, or such calculation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조화 [조ː화]</dt><br>
<dd>1. workings; harmony</dd><br>
<dd>이 세상의 모든 것을 만들고 기르는 대자연의 이치. 또는 그런 이치에 따라 만들어진 모든 것.</dd><br>
<dd>The law of mother nature that creates and raises all the things in the world, or everything created in accordance with the law of nature.</dd><br>
<dd>2. magic</dd><br>
<dd>어떻게 이루어진 것인지 알 수 없을 정도로 이상하고 신기한 일. 또는 그런 일을 꾸미는 재주.</dd><br>
<dd>Something so strange and mysterious that it is impossible to find out how it happened, or an ability to make such a thing happen.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>융화 [융화]</dt><br>
<dd>harmony</dd><br>
<dd>서로 어울려 다툼이 없이 화목하게 됨.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of peaceful coexistence without a dispute.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>